parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the fuel pump flange or housing can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when the fuel drips onto the hot engine or exhaust pipes.
symptoms: fuel dripping onto the engine or exhaust pipes
cracks in the fuel pump flange or housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Fuel Pump Flange/Fuel Connector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracked fuel pump flange or fuel connector failure can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when riding at high speeds. This can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel pump flange or fuel connector
severe fuel leaks at the fuel tank flange.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents. It can also result in costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: The final drive seizes or fails
causing the vehicle to become undrivable
oil leaks or spills from the final drive
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear of the vehicle.
